title: Miller Man Faces Sex Trafficking Charge
text:
Miller Man Faces Sex Trafficking Charge October 19, 2015, 1:58 PM PIERRE, SD - 
An sex trafficking operation in Pierre led to an arrest. 
Attorney General Marty Jackley said 34-year-old Joseph Raymond Raleigh, of Miller, is charged with one count of attempted commercial sex trafficking. He faces a minimum of 10 years if convicted. 
The Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force and U.S. Marshals Service conducted an undercover operation from October 16 to 18. 
The Pierre Police Department assisted in the operation. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
